{\pard\sb280\sa120\keepn\f0\fs36\cf2\b {\*\bkmkstart quick-start}Quick Start{\*\bkmkend quick-start}\par}
{\pard\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\fs30\cf2\b {\*\bkmkstart 1-copy-the-action-into-your-repo}1. Copy the action into your repo{\*\bkmkend 1-copy-the-action-into-your-repo}\par}
{\pard\sb100\sa100\f1\fs20\cbpat8\li360\ri360 mkdir -p .github/actions/readme-to-rtf\line
cp action.yml gfm_markdown_to_rtf.py rtf_image_embedder.py .github/actions/readme-to-rtf/\line
\par}
{\pard\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\fs30\cf2\b {\*\bkmkstart 2-add-the-workflow}2. Add the workflow{\*\bkmkend 2-add-the-workflow}\par}
{\pard\sb0\sa120\f0\fs22 Create {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 .github/workflows/readme-to-rtf.yml}:\par}
{\pard\sb100\sa100\f1\fs20\cbpat8\li360\ri360 \cf18 name\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  Convert README to RTF\line
\line
\cf18 on\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1 \line
  \cf18 workflow_dispatch\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1 \line
  \cf18 push\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1 \line
    \cf18 paths\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1 \line
      \cf23 -\cf1  \cf19 '\cf1 \cf19 README.md\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \line
\line
\cf18 jobs\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1 \line
  \cf18 convert\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1 \line
    \cf18 runs-on\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  ubuntu-latest\line
    \cf18 permissions\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1 \line
      \cf18 contents\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  write\line
    \cf18 steps\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1 \line
      \cf23 -\cf1  \cf18 uses\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  actions/checkout@v4\line
\line
      \cf23 -\cf1  \cf18 name\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  Convert README to RTF\line
        \cf18 uses\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  ./.github/actions/readme-to-rtf\line
\line
      \cf23 -\cf1  \cf18 name\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  Configure git\line
        \cf18 shell\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  bash\line
        \cf18 run\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  git config user.name "github-actions[bot]"\line
\line
      \cf23 -\cf1  \cf18 name\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  Configure git email\line
        \cf18 shell\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  bash\line
        \cf18 run\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  git config user.email "github-actions[bot]@users.noreply.github.com"\line
\line
      \cf23 -\cf1  \cf18 name\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  Stage RTF\line
        \cf18 shell\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  bash\line
        \cf18 run\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  git add README.rtf\line
\line
      \cf23 -\cf1  \cf18 name\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  Commit if changed\line
        \cf18 shell\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  bash\line
        \cf18 run\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  \cf19 '\cf1 \cf19 git\cf1  \cf19 diff\cf1  \cf19 --cached\cf1  \cf19 --quiet\cf1  \cf19 ||\cf1  \cf19 git\cf1  \cf19 commit\cf1  \cf19 -m\cf1  \cf19 "auto-regenerate\cf1  \cf19 README.rtf\cf1  \cf19 from\cf1  \cf19 README.md"\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \line
\line
      \cf23 -\cf1  \cf18 name\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  Push\line
        \cf18 shell\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  bash\line
        \cf18 run\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  git push\line
\par}
{\pard\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\fs30\cf2\b {\*\bkmkstart 3-push-and-done}3. Push and done{\*\bkmkend 3-push-and-done}\par}
{\pard\sb0\sa120\f0\fs22 Every time {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 README.md} changes, the workflow generates a fresh {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 README.rtf} and commits it to your repo. You can also trigger it manually from the Actions tab.\par}
{\pard\sb280\sa120\keepn\f0\fs36\cf2\b {\*\bkmkstart how-it-works}How It Works{\*\bkmkend how-it-works}\par}
{\pard\sb0\sa120\f0\fs22 Two Python scripts, zero heavy dependencies:\par}
{\pard\sb36\sa36\li480\fi-360\f0\fs22 1.  {\b {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 gfm_markdown_to_rtf.py}} \u8212? Parses GitHub-Flavored Markdown and generates RTF with a data-driven rule engine. Uses {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://pygments.org/"}{\fldrslt \cf2 Pygments}} for syntax highlighting. Resolves {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 @mentions} and {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 #issues} to GitHub URLs automatically.\par}
{\pard\sb36\sa36\li480\fi-360\f0\fs22 2.  {\b {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 rtf_image_embedder.py}} \u8212? Standalone module that finds {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 [Image: ...]} placeholders in RTF, reads the referenced local images, downscales them to fit page bounds using {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://pillow.readthedocs.io/"}{\fldrslt \cf2 Pillow}}, and embeds them as hex-encoded {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 ␀ESC:\pict} blocks.\par}
{\pard\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\fs30\cf2\b {\*\bkmkstart dependencies}Dependencies{\*\bkmkend dependencies}\par}
{\pard\sb36\sa36\li480\fi-360\f0\fs22 \u8226?  {\b Python 3} (preinstalled on GitHub Actions runners)\par}
{\pard\sb36\sa36\li480\fi-360\f0\fs22 \u8226?  {\b Pygments} ({\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 pip install pygments}) \u8212? syntax highlighting for 500+ languages\par}
{\pard\sb36\sa36\li480\fi-360\f0\fs22 \u8226?  {\b Pillow} ({\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 pip install pillow}) \u8212? image processing for embedding and downscaling\par}
{\pard\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\fs30\cf2\b {\*\bkmkstart run-locally}Run Locally{\*\bkmkend run-locally}\par}
{\pard\sb100\sa100\f1\fs20\cbpat8\li360\ri360 pip install pygments pillow\line
python3 gfm_markdown_to_rtf.py README.md README.rtf\line
python3 rtf_image_embedder.py README.rtf\line
\par}
{\pard\sb280\sa120\keepn\f0\fs36\cf2\b {\*\bkmkstart viewing-tips}Viewing Tips{\*\bkmkend viewing-tips}\par}
{\pard\sb0\sa120\f0\fs22 When opening the RTF in LibreOffice Writer:\par}
{\pard\sb36\sa36\li480\fi-360\f0\fs22 \u8226?  {\b Disable red squiggles}: Tools > Automatic Spell Checking (toggle off)\par}
{\pard\sb36\sa36\li480\fi-360\f0\fs22 \u8226?  {\b Read-only mode}: Edit > Edit Mode (toggle off) for a clean reading view\par}
{\pard\sb36\sa36\li480\fi-360\f0\fs22 \u8226?  {\b Full screen}: {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 Ctrl+Shift+J}\par}
